<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-51-1132 </DOCNO><TEXT>A relativistic generalization of Rabi's formula for magnetic resonanceis given. On this basis, we consider fast and slow passage through resonance.We define a magnetic resonance exterior field as usual, using unit vectorsof a Cartesian coordinate system, a homogeneous magnetic field, and theamplitude of a rotating magnetic field. For the description of spin dynamicswe use the Bargmann-Michel-Telegdi equation.</TEXT></DOC>